TopicTitle: [1.8.x] DMagic Orbital Science: New Science Parts [v1.4.3] [11/2/2019]

Articles.Content:
It looks like the solar particle collector is impossible to get in career (using community tech tree). I have "advanced construction" unlocked but the part doesnt appear in the science catagory

edit: my mistake, i was reading it wrong. It's under Long Term Science

Edited May 30, 2016 by cineboxandrew

Hi, I got a problem with DMagicOrbitalScience and the Science parts for UniversalStorage. I just can't get them to work. They seem to have the correct model, but they don't react to right clicks neither in the VAB nor on the launchpad.

The installation path of the both mods are correct, so i don't see any reason, why it doesn't work. I tried to put the Science parts into the UniversalStorage folder, but that didn't help, they even had the wrong model.

...\Kerbal Space Program\GameData\DMagicOrbitalScience\UniversalStorage

...\Kerbal Space Program\GameData\UniversalStorage\Parts

i searched a while in both release threats for similar issues, but coulds't find a solution.

Maybe one of you guys can help.

@Bishop149 Does the KSPedia entry above clear up the seismic hammer issue? 

I'll look into the second point, those double experiment parts are a  little weird.

@the1visionary Do you have log files from when this happens? That definitely isn't normal.

@Nithos Do you have log files? Moving the files around won't work. Do the other parts work normally?

Alright so I am having issues with the parts. I can't run the science experiments from any of them.

@JewelShisen

It's very hard to diagnose the problem from what you've written and the experts will need a little more information than "It's not working".  Confirm you have the latest version of the mod, from the information either from the website, AVP or CKAN (Orbital Science is on v1.3 IIRC).  Confirm that you've installed it correctly (you might describe how you  installed it).  Describe what exactly you've encountered.  Do you get the right-click menu entry for the part?  Posting a picture of the problem and a link to your KSP log file, on something such as Dropbox, can help, too.

The Magnetometer still functions for an Ore scanner but that is it. Right clicking it shows Ore levels and that is all, no button to deploy it, no button for the science tests, nothing.

Hi @DMagic, I can't thank you enough for making such a wonderful mod. Are there any plans for making parts for the Octosat mod in a similar fashion to those in universal storage?

On 1/6/2014 at 6:01 AM, DMagic said:

The magnetometer functions as a crude anomaly detector for those not using SCANsat or any other method for detecting anomalies. Watch for spikes in the magnetic field readings found in the magnetometer's right-click context menu.

 Hi i started using using this mod recently. Is there any graphical representation of the magnetic sensor data ,because you said to watch out for spikes , spikes on what ? Because if there is, mod is broken in my machine

@einstein72 Nope. 

@Apurva Kawthalkar Right click on the magnetometer when it's deployed, it will show the magnetic field read-out, though you're better off using something like SCANsat to find anomaly locations.
